Let's say a trade happens on Monday 17th Feb:
Trade flow:

Book: Books the trade on Monday (T) — so Book intraday feed picks it up Monday
RMS/FO: Books the trade on Tuesday (T+1) — so RMS intraday feed picks it up Tuesday

What happens in your three screens:

INTRADAY screen (Monday):

Book side: Trade shows up ✅
RMS side: Nothing yet ❌
Result: Unmatched Book trade — this is a break

INTRADAY screen (Tuesday):

RMS trade now comes in and matches off against the Book trade from Monday
Result: Matched ✅


T+1 screen (Tuesday — processing Monday COB):

Book T+1 EOD feed: Has the trade ✅
RMS accumulated intraday: Doesn't have it yet (RMS only books it Tuesday) ❌
Result: T+1 break

T+1 screen (Wednesday — processing Tuesday COB):

Monday's T+1 break rolls forward
RMS now has the trade from Tuesday's intraday
Result: Matched ✅


P&L screen (Tuesday — showing Monday COB):

Book MTD PL: Includes P&L from this trade (booked Monday)
FO MTD PL: Doesn't have it (RMS only booked Tuesday)
Result: P&L break 

P&L screen (Wednesday — showing Tuesday COB):

Both sides now have the trade
Result: Should match ✅
